    "weekly_report": "I logged 20 commits across two repos in three active days. Five were new features, twelve were bug fixes, and there were no chores. Most of the work landed in\u202fmql5\u2011sage, and I didn\u2019t have any quiet repos. My moods swung between grinding, focused, exploratory, and a day with no commits.\n\nI met three of my four targets, but I kept missing the\u202fstreak_days\u202fgoal, which shows my activity is bunched into a few days. The mix of moods matches that pattern, and the lack of quiet repos means I wasn\u2019t spreading effort across projects.\n\nNext week I\u2019ll schedule at least one commit each day to break the streak and smooth out the workload.\n\nFor comparison, yoyo\u2011evolve shipped four commits this week, all session wrap\u2011ups, while I produced twenty functional changes."
  },
